\b Intelligent Data Quality Engine (IDQE)\b0\line
\b Installation Guide for Enterprise Test and Production Environments\b0\line
\line
Version: 1.0\line
Date: February 7, 2026\line
Document Path: ./docs/install-enterprise.pdf\line
\line
\b 1. Scope\b0\line
This guide describes how to deploy IDQE in:\line
- Enterprise Test environment\line
- Enterprise Production environment\line
\line
It covers architecture, prerequisites, security, deployment steps, validation, and operations handover.\line
\line
\b 2. Components\b0\line
IDQE consists of:\line
- workflow-client (web UI with tabs for workflow, rules editor, MCP session, LLM config)\line
- mcp-server (MCP orchestration, data source access, workflow tracking, rule/LLM config APIs)\line
- dq-engine (DQ assessment and correction service)\line
- PostgreSQL (workflow run metadata and demo/test data source)\line
\line
Main configuration files:\line
- ./config/rules.prod.yaml\line
- ./config/llm.prod.yaml\line
\line
\b 3. Enterprise Architecture (Recommended)\b0\line
Use containerized services on Kubernetes:\line
- Namespace isolation: idqe\line
- Ingress/API gateway in front of workflow-client and mcp-server\line
- Managed PostgreSQL (HA, backups, encryption)\line
- Secret manager for API keys and DB credentials\line
- Centralized logs, metrics, traces\line
- CI/CD with signed images and vulnerability scans\line
\line
Provided manifests:\line
- ./deploy/k8s/namespace.yaml\line
- ./deploy/k8s/dq-engine.yaml\line
- ./deploy/k8s/mcp-server.yaml\line
- ./deploy/k8s/workflow-client.yaml\line
- ./deploy/k8s/configmap-llm.yaml\line
\line
\b 4. Prerequisites\b0\line
\b 4.1 Test Environment\b0\line
- Kubernetes cluster (non-production)\line
- Container registry and pull access\line
- PostgreSQL test instance\line
- DNS route or internal ingress\line
- TLS certificate for test domain\line
\line
\b 4.2 Production Environment\b0\line
- Production Kubernetes cluster with HA worker pools\line
- Managed PostgreSQL with PITR backups\line
- Enterprise secret management (Vault/KMS/cloud secret manager)\line
- WAF/API gateway and network policies\line
- SIEM/SOC integration for logs and alerts\line
- Change management approval before release\line
\line
\b 5. Build and Publish Container Images\b0\line
From repository root:\line
\f1
cd .\line
docker build -f services/dq-engine/Dockerfile -t <registry>/idqe-dq-engine:1.0.0 .\line
docker build -f services/mcp-server/Dockerfile -t <registry>/idqe-mcp-server:1.0.0 .\line
docker build -f services/workflow-client/Dockerfile -t <registry>/idqe-workflow-client:1.0.0 services/workflow-client\line
docker push <registry>/idqe-dq-engine:1.0.0\line
docker push <registry>/idqe-mcp-server:1.0.0\line
docker push <registry>/idqe-workflow-client:1.0.0\line
\f0
\line
\b 6. Configure Environment-Specific Values\b0\line
\b 6.1 Rules\b0\line
- Test: start from ./config/rules.demo.yaml\line
- Production: use ./config/rules.prod.yaml\line
\line
\b 6.2 LLM\b0\line
- Test: set provider=mock or a sandbox key\line
- Production: set provider=openai and production key controls\line
- File: ./config/llm.prod.yaml\line
\line
\b 6.3 Secrets\b0\line
Never store API keys in Git.\line
Store secrets via Kubernetes secrets or external secret manager:\line
- Database URL\line
- OPENAI_API_KEY (if openai provider is enabled)\line
\line
\b 7. Deploy to Enterprise Test\b0\line
\f1
kubectl apply -f deploy/k8s/namespace.yaml\line
kubectl -n idqe create secret generic idqe-db --from-literal=database_url='postgresql+psycopg2://<user>:<pass>@<host>:5432/dq'\line
kubectl -n idqe create configmap idqe-llm-config --from-file=llm.yaml=config/llm.prod.yaml -o yaml --dry-run=client | kubectl apply -f -\line
kubectl apply -f deploy/k8s/dq-engine.yaml\line
kubectl apply -f deploy/k8s/mcp-server.yaml\line
kubectl apply -f deploy/k8s/workflow-client.yaml\line
\f0
\line
Update image tags in manifests to your registry path before applying.\line
\line
\b 8. Test Environment Validation Checklist\b0\line
- workflow-client reachable via ingress\line
- mcp-server and dq-engine health endpoints return status ok\line
- MCP Session tab can connect and list tools\line
- Run Workflow executes assessment/correction\line
- Workflow history row click opens details\line
- DQ Rules Editor load/save works\line
- LLM Config load/save works\line
- Suggestion queue popup appears when LLM enabled\line
- Approve suggestion persists new rule and affects next runs\line
\line
\b 9. Deploy to Production\b0\line
Production rollout recommendation:\line
1. Deploy to pre-prod and run full regression\line
2. Deploy production with rolling update strategy\line
3. Enable canary traffic (10% then 50% then 100%)\line
4. Monitor errors, latency, DQ pipeline throughput\line
5. Execute rollback plan immediately on threshold breach\line
\line
Mandatory production controls:\line
- TLS everywhere (ingress and service mesh where applicable)\line
- RBAC for rule and LLM config edits\line
- Audit logging for rule approvals/declines\line
- Daily backups and tested restore procedure\line
- Alerting on service health and failed workflow runs\line
\line
\b 10. Operations and Support\b0\line
Daily operations:\line
- Review failed workflow runs\line
- Review new LLM suggestions and approval decisions\line
- Monitor DQ quality index trend\line
\line
Recommended SLOs:\line
- API uptime: 99.9%\line
- Assessment request p95 latency < 3 seconds\line
- Failed workflow run rate < 1%\line
\line
\b 11. Rollback\b0\line
- Rollback deployment image tags to last known good release\line
- Restore previous rules/LLM config from versioned backup\line
- Verify health and rerun smoke tests\line
\line
\b 12. Appendix: Quick Commands\b0\line
